  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Beam and Bombardment weapons</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Phaerax are tall, slender insectoid creatures with a
  sandy-colored exoskeleton. The Phaerax resemble the various flora on their
  home planet Phaeros and have a curious way of moving which emulates the
  various plants under different weather conditions.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>On their home planet the Phaerax evolved to camoufla=
ge
  themselves from the many giant predators. The giant Draxis Lizards were t=
he
  biggest threat to the Phaerax and other similar-sized insects. The Draxis
  only exist in zoos now, hunted to extinction in the wild.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Phaerax have developed the ability to transmit m=
icro
  waves with their own body to cook their food and to kill. Exceptional
  warriors the Phaerax are deadly in close quarters.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Phaerax have a natural strong motivation to ensu=
re
  they are on the winning side of any struggle. Thus, the Phaerax do not ma=
ke
  reliable allies although they will often appear friendly to the strong or
  where it helps them.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Phaerax society lives in elaborate glass tunnels und=
er the
  sand, having become masters at drilling underground.</p>
